"Abstract “E-commerce is seeing rapid growth both for companies as well as for consumers. But without security and trust, financial and commercial transactions via the Internet will not see decisive growth,” 1 declared the European Commissioner for the Information Society on the adoption of a European directive on electronic signatures. The development of e-business has been held back for a long time in France and Europe by a legal structure which is not adapted to new technologies. Reform has come from the European Commission and it is currently continuing in the Member States. We shall analyse below the basic principles of the reform established by the Directive of December 13, 1999, concerning a Community framework for electronic signatures, 2 as well as how the new French legislation is dealing with this issue."
